    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(13) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Thou shalt be perfect with the Lord thy God.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—Rashi’s note on this is worth preserving: “Thou shalt walk with Him in sincerity, and wait for Him. And thou shalt not pry into the future. But whatsoever cometh upon thee, take it with simplicity, and then thou shalt ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "be with Him, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and be His portion.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
